Casirivimab and imdevimab should be administered by a healthcare worker in a monitored clinical setting intravenously through an infusion (drip). In some instances, the medication may be given subcutaneously through an injection. The dosage of the medication will be determined by the healthcare provider. For patients with non-severe COVID-19 the total dose of casirivimab and imdevimab is 1200 – 2400 mg given once intravenously. Alternatively, a patient may receive a total one-time dose of 1200 mg subcutaneously. For patients with severe or critical COVID-19 the total dose of casirivimab and imdevimab is 2400 – 8000 mg given once intravenously.  
